rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all administrative bodies in cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Administrative Body

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket administrative body to the country where the administrative body has authority.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Jurisdiction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket administrative body to a cricket team that is a member of the administrative body.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket administrative body to a recurring championship event that is sponsored by the administrative body.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tournament

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of batting strokes. Batting strokes are used to score runs or prevent the loss of the wicket. Batting tactics and strategy depend on the type of cricket being played, as well as the state of the game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Batting Stroke

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all cricket bowlers, a type of cricket player. Bowlers are those cricket player skilled at propelling the ball toward the wicket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Bowler

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket bowler to the typical pace of the bowler, e.g. medium fast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pace

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a cricket bowler to his professional career statistics. Cricket statistics are computed by form of cricket, so a cricket bowler may be related to multiple sets of information based on form of cricket, e.g. ODI, test or T20.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bowling Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies whether the cricket bowler is left-handed, right-handed or ambidextrous.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bowling Style

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket bowler to a standard descriptor for a technique used by the bowler, e.g. 'lob bowling', 'finger spin', and 'right-arm leg spin'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Technique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects statistical information about the performance of a cricket bowler.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Bowler Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of balls bowled by the given cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Balls Bowled

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the best ratio of the number of wickets over the fewest runs conceded for the number of wickets in two or more innings of a match bowled by the given player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Best Bowling In a Match

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the best ratio of the number of wickets over the fewest runs conceded for the number of wickets in one inning of a match bowled by the given player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Best Bowling in an Inning

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the best ratio of the number of wickets over the fewest runs conceded for the number of wickets in a game bowled by the given player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Best Record

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the average number of runs conceded per wicket by the given player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bowling Average

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a cricket player's statistics in a given form of cricket to the given form of cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the average number of runs conceded per over for the given player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Economy Rate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of innings in which the given player took at least five wickets.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Five Wicket Haul

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of times that the given bowler has taken three wickets with three consecutive deliveries.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hat Tricks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of over bowled by the given player. An over in cricket is a set of six balls bowled from one end of a cricket pitch.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a cricket player's statistics in a given form of cricket to the cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of runs conceded by the given player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Runs Against

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the average number of balls bowled per wicket taken by the given player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Strike Rate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of matches in which the given player took at least ten wickets.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ten Wicket Haul

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of wickets taken by the given bowler.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wickets

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of bowling paces. Kinds of bowling pace include 'fast', 'medium fast', and 'slow'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Bowling Pace

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a standard descriptor for a bowling pace, e.g. medium fast, to the maximum speed in kilometers per hour of the bowling pace.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a standard descriptor for a bowling pace, e.g. medium fast, to the minimum speed in kilometers per hour of the bowling pace.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of bowling techniques. These include 'lob bowling', 'finger spin', and 'right-arm leg spin'. Bowling in cricket is the act of propelling the ball toward the wicket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Bowling Technique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The captain of a cricket team determines the strategy and tactics of the team. In particular, the cricket captain, unlike the cricket coach, is responsible for all decisions made in the course of a game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Captain

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket captain to career statistics for the captain in the Twenty20 format of cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overall T20 Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket captain to career statistics for the captain in the ODI (One-Day International) format of cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overall ODI Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket captain to career statistics for the captain in the Test format of cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overall Test Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket captain to information about the teams with which the captain has been affiliated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Teams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the teams with which a cricket captain is affiliated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Captain Tenure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the statistics for the team in the Twenty20 format of cricket when the given captain was affiliated with the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: T20 Stats
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use cricket.captain_tenure.team_stats intead. The match type can be specified with cricket.captain_tenure.competition_form. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:cricket.captain_tenure.team_stats]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the cricket captain about which team affiliation information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Captain

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the form of cricket played, e.g. ODI, Test, and T20, by the corresponding team during the tenure of the given captain.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competition Form

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date on which the captain ceased to be captain of the given team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the statistics for the team in the ODI (One-Day International) format of cricket when the given captain was affiliated with the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: ODI Stats
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use cricket.captain_tenure.team_stats intead. The match type can be specified with cricket.captain_tenure.competition_form. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:cricket.captain_tenure.team_stats]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date on which the captain first became captain of the given team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Start Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the team with which the given cricket captain was affiliated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies statistics relating to the teams of which the given person was a captain.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the statistics for the team in the Test format of cricket when the given captain was affiliated with the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Test Stats
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use cricket.captain_tenure.team_stats intead. The match type can be specified with cricket.captain_tenure.competition_form. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:cricket.captain_tenure.team_stats]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all coaches of cricket teams. Currently this collection includes all professional cricket coaches, as well as non-professional cricket coaches.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Coach

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket coach to career statistics for the coach in the ODI (One-Day International) format of cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overall ODI Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket coach to career statistics for the coach in the Test format of cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overall Test Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a cricket coach to statistics about the teams which he or she has coached.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a cricket coach to information about the teams with which the coach has been affiliated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Teams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the teams with which a cricket coach is affiliated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Coach Tenure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the cricket coach about which tenure information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coach

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the last date that the given coach held the given position.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date
ODI Stats
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use cricket.coach_tenure.team_stats instead. The competition form can be specified with cricket.team_stats.match_type. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:cricket.coach_tenure.team_stats]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the given coach first held the given position.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Start Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the team of which the person was coach during the given time frame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies statistics relating to the team of which the given person was a coach.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team Statistics
Test Stats
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use cricket.coach_tenure.team_stats instead. The competition form can be specified with cricket.team_stats.match_type. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:cricket.coach_tenure.team_stats]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all cricket delivery type. These include 'lob bowling', 'off cutter', and 'bouncer'. Delivery in cricket is a single act of bowling, which is propelling the ball toward the batsman.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Delivery Type
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This seems to be a duplicate of cricket.bowling_technique. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:cricket.bowling_technique]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of dismissals in cricket. These include 'caught', 'bowled', and 'retired out'. Dismissal in cricket refers to when the batsman is out of play for that inning.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dismissal Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about a wicket being hit by a bowler when a player is a bat.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fall Of Wicket

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the cricket player at bat.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batsman

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the over, a set of six balls, in which the wicket is put down by the bowler.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Over

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the score of the match when the wicket is put down.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of the wicket that is put down.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wicket Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all cricket leagues. These are the organized competitions of cricket games, usually culminating into a winner of the league.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket League
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type overlaps with both cricket.administrative_body and cricket.tournament. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:cricket.administrative_body]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all cricket matches. Cricket matches are played by two teams with each team taking turns at bat. Each turn is known as an inning, and the number of innings in any given match depends on the type of cricket match being played. For example, first-class cricket has a duration of three to five days. In contrast, limited-overs cricket only allows each team to play one inning , and a game of this form of cricket lasts at most a day. Finally, some forms of cricket like Twenty20 are designed to last only about three hours.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Match

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to the time interval over which the match was played.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to an official who has the authority to make judgments about the game on the field.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Field Umpires

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to the team in the match that batted first.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Batting Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to the player whose performance was deemed most outstanding in the match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Man of the Match

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to the referee of the match. Note that a referee, unlike a field umpire, only ensures that the cricket code of conduct is observed and enforced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Match Referee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to a standard descriptor for the type of match, viz. one-day international (or ODI), test or T20.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Match Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to the number of overs in the match. An over is a set of six balls bowled from one end of a cricket pitch.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a match to team-specific and inning-specific information for the match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team Roster

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a cricket match to a series event that includes the match. A cricket series is a group of cricket matches played in test cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Series Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to the stadium where the match was played.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stadium

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to the third umpire of the match. The third umpire in a cricket match decides any issues that are referred to him or her by the two field umpires.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Third Umpire

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to the team that won the toss of the match, which determines which team will be allowed to bat first.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Toss Winner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a cricket match to a tournament event if any that includes the cricket match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tournament Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match to the team that won the match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Winner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the types of cricket matches played. There are multiple kinds of matches that are based on the playing standard, level of formality, and desired amount of playing time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Match Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match type to the number of innings played by each team in a match of this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Innings Per Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match type to the maximum duration of each inning in a match of this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Duration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket match type to the number of overs that make up an inning in a match of this type. An over in cricket is a set of six balls bowled from one end of a cricket pitch.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overs per Inning

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all professional cricket players. Typically, cricket players are considered bowlers or batsmen. The exceptional player who is good at both is called an all-rounder.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that specifies whether the player performs well at both batting and bowling in cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: All Rounder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies whether the cricket player is left-handed, right-handed or ambidextrous.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batting Style

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket player to one of the positions held by the player in his or her career, e.g. batter or bowler.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a cricket player to his professional career statistics. Cricket statistics are computed by form of cricket, so a cricket player may be related to multiple sets of information based on form of cricket, e.g. ODI, test or T20.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the first professional appearance of a given cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Player Debut

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date of the first professional appearance of the given cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the match in which the given cricket player first played professionally.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Match

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a cricket player's debut information with career statistics for the player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects statistical information about cricket players in general and cricket batters in particular.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Player Stats

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies The total number of balls received by the given batter, including no balls but not including wides.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Balls Faced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of runs of the batter divided by the total number of innings in which the batter was out.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batting Average

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of catches taken by the given cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Catches

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of innings in which the batter scored one hundred runs or more.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Centuries

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a cricket player's statistics in a given form of cricket to the form of cricket. Common forms of cricket include Test cricket, ODI, and first class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of innings in which the batter scored 50 to 99 runs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Half Centuries

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of innings in which the batter batted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Innings

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of matches played by the given cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Matches

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of times the batter was not out at the end of an inning in which he or she batted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Not Outs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a cricket player's statistics in a form of cricket to the player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying information about the first professional appearance of the given cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Debut

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of run outs of the given cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Run Outs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of runs scored by the given cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Runs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the overall average of runs scored per 100 balls faced by the given cricket player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Strike Rate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a cricket player's statistics in a form of cricket to the number of stumpings made as a wicket-keeper in that type of cricket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stumps

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the highest score ever made by the given batter in a match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the highest score of the given cricket player occurred in a match where the player had no outs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Score Not Out

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for roles on a cricket team, e.g. batter and bowler.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects statistics about a particular team during a particular inning of a given cricket match. Properties on this type include the batting roster, bowling roster, and fall of wicket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Roster

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies information about each batting episode of a cricket match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batting

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the captain of the team for the given roster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Captain

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the coach of the team for the given roster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coach

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that provides information about a wicket that was put down when the given team was at bat.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fall Of Wicket

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the inning of the cricket match for which roster information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Inning

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies information about each bowling episode of a cricket match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bowling

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the match for which roster information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Roster in Match
Keeping

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about who was at bat during a given inning of a given cricket match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Roster Batting

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the ball if any hit by the player during the given inning of the given cricket match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Balls

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the bowler for the given player of the given inning of the given match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bowled

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the player, if any, who caught the batted ball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Caught by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the manner if any in which the given batter was dismissed by the bowler.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of cricket series. A cricket series is a group of cricket matches played in test cricket, see also cricket.match. Matches in this type of cricket can last up to five days, and the series can consist of three to five matches. Entities of this type may or may not also be typed with cricket.tournament.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Series

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of specific cricket series events. These are the specific instances of series, for example the 2013 Ashes series and the 1981 Benson and Hedges World Cup in cricket. An entity typed with cricket.series_event may or may not also be typed with cricket.tournament_event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Series Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cricket series event to the time interval when the event was held.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dates

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Match

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a cricket series event to the series of which it is a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Series

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all kinds of cricket tournaments. A cricket tournament is a championship event between cricket teams that occurs on a regular basis. Entities with this type include the Cricket World Cup and the Duleep Trophy. For entities of specific tournaments played, see cricket.tournament_event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Tournament

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a cricket tournament to a tournament event that is a part of it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all specific cricket tournaments played. Entities with this type include the 2012 ICC World Twenty20 and the 2003 Cricket World Cup. For entities of the types of cricket tournaments, see also cricket.tournament.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Tournament Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a cricket tournament event to the time interval when the event was held.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dates

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Match

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of cricket umpires. Note that this type includes both referees and field umpires. A field umpire makes judgments on the field, keeps a record of the deliveries, and announces the completion of an over. A referee, on the other hand, only ensures that the cricket code of conduct is observed and enforced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cricket Umpire
